texts.text: Java Edition data values/Protocol and data versions

Protocol versions are used to identify a game version over the network, such that only compatible versions may connect with each other. Data versions indicate the version of the game a world was saved with, so that it can be upgraded to newest version.
Protocol version numbers before the 13w41a reset due to Netty rewrite.
Changes from April Fools' versions were not kept in later versions.
